1. Traffic Anomalies

    Unusually High Traffic: Sudden spikes in web traffic.
    Unusually Low Traffic: Unexpected drops in web traffic.
    Traffic from Suspicious IPs: Access attempts from known malicious IP addresses.
    Unusual Geographic Traffic: Traffic coming from unexpected geographic locations.
    High Number of Requests from Single IP: Excessive requests from a single IP address.

2. Error Anomalies

    High Rate of 404 Errors: Frequent "Page Not Found" errors.
    High Rate of 500 Errors: Frequent server errors indicating internal issues.
    High Rate of 403 Errors: Frequent access denied errors.
    Frequent Database Connection Errors: Issues connecting to the database.
    Frequent Timeout Errors: Requests that exceed the serverâ€™s timeout limit.


======================================================================================================================

1. Performance Anomalies

    High server response time
    Slow page load times
    Excessive CPU usage
    High memory consumption
    Disk I/O spikes
    Server timeout errors (504 Gateway Timeout)
    High error rates (500 Internal Server Error)
    Slow database queries affecting web performance
    Connection pooling issues
    Resource exhaustion (CPU, memory, disk)

2. Security Anomalies

    Unauthorized login attempts
    SQL injection attempts
    Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attempts
    Directory traversal attacks
    Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks
    Suspicious file uploads
    Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) attacks
    Brute-force attack detection
    Web shell uploads
    Insecure API access attempts

3. Network Anomalies

    Unusual outbound traffic spikes
    Unresolved DNS requests
    Network latency spikes
    TCP connection reset anomalies
    High number of open connections
    IP address spoofing attempts
    Unusual port scans
    SYN flood attacks
    Packet loss
    Unexpected network protocol usage

4. Application Anomalies

    Application crashes
    Memory leaks in applications
    High database connection count
    Missing or corrupted web content
    Error in application logic leading to data inconsistency
    Application resource deadlocks
    Unresponsive application components
    Excessive log generation by an application
    Application startup delays
    Malformed HTTP requests

5. Configuration Anomalies

    Misconfigured SSL/TLS settings
    Missing or expired SSL certificates
    Incorrect file permissions on web directories
    Incorrect DNS configuration
    Improper load balancer settings
    HTTP headers missing security directives (e.g., Content Security Policy)
    Unintentional server configuration changes
    Web server configuration files tampering
    Incorrect session management settings
    Misconfigured application parameters

6. Log Anomalies

    Sudden spikes in error log entries
    Unusual patterns in access logs
    404 errors increase significantly
    Log file rotation failures
    Unauthorized access log entries
    Unusual IP addresses accessing the server
    Log entries from unrecognized user agents
    Sudden changes in log file size
    Log entries with non-standard status codes
    Frequent login/logout patterns in logs

7. User Behavior Anomalies

    Unusual login patterns (e.g., different locations in a short time)
    Abnormal user session durations
    Frequent password reset requests
    Suspicious user registration activity
    Unauthorized access to admin panels
    Excessive form submission attempts
    Unusual API usage patterns by users
    Multiple failed login attempts
    Unusual data download activity
    Abnormal user access times

8. Content Delivery Anomalies

    Issues with CDN integration
    Cache miss anomalies leading to slow content delivery
    Stale content being served
    Inconsistent content across different regions
    Content not being updated in real-time
    Failures in content replication to CDN nodes
    Content delivery delays during peak hours
    Abnormal spikes in content delivery requests
    Misrouting of content to incorrect regions
    Inconsistent content compression

9. Database Anomalies

    Slow query execution times
    Database connection timeout errors
    High number of failed database transactions
    Inconsistent data reads/writes
    Database deadlocks
    Unauthorized database access attempts
    Missing database indices leading to performance issues
    Database replication failures
    Database corruption issues
    High database load affecting web server performance

10. Miscellaneous Anomalies

    Unexpected server reboots
    Backup failures
    Resource allocation issues in virtualized environments
    Unusual patterns in third-party API interactions
    High number of redirects causing poor user experience
    Unusual server start/stop events
    Unstable third-party service integrations
    Unusual peaks in web traffic (potential bots)
    Unrecognized devices accessing the server
    Disk space exhaustion due to log file growth
